Of the support group participants: Two were injured three or four years before the start of the project, four were injured between 8 and 17 years prior to the study, and two were injured more than 25 years prior. Six have survived traumatic brain injuries, and two have survived brain tumors. Participants ranged in age from 40 to 60 years old; five are women and three are men. All are living with disability from brain injury.
For the support group participants, inclusion/exclusion criteria included: 
membership in the support group;
interesting in participating;
ability and willingness to adhere to the activity's ethical guidelines;
ability and willingness to commit to attending all support group photovoice meetings.
